ABUJA  – Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami (SAN), has described as false media reports (not Daily Independent) that he had conclusively exonerated Abba Kyari of any wrongful act in the alleged cocaine deal. The clarification was made by Dr. Umar Jibrilu Gwandu, Special Assistant on Media and Public Relations, Office of the Attorney General of the Federation and Minister of Justice. In a statement on Sunday, Malami claimed “there appears to be misunderstanding regarding the issue. “It was a case of work in progress in respect of which the Office of the Attorney General of the Federation requested for further probe in relation to some aspects of investigation”, Malami stated. The statement released by his media aide, Dr, Umar Gwandu, said, “It was clear that the conclusion on the alleged contradiction on the issue was a clear case of misconception. “The Office of the Attorney General of the Federation and Minister of Justice’s stance is that no conclusion has been reached in the absence of evidence relating to the first report. “The issues were raised for further investigation with a view to cover the field in investigation in order to arrive at an informed decision”, the AGF said.